Convert-Age

A simple module to with functions to convert integers representing
a number of seconds into a form using years, days, hours and seconds.

Eg: 189988007 becomes 6y7d10h26m47s
    and 5h39m becomes 20340

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    perldoc Convert::Age

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Convert-Age

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Convert-Age

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Convert-Age

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Convert-Age

